  "prompt": "What are the top 10 inspirational movies of the 21st century?",
  "response": "Here are ten inspirational movies from the 21st century that have resonated with audiences through their powerful storytelling, uplifting themes, and motivating characters:\n\n1. **The Pursuit of Happyness (2006)** - Based on the true story of Chris Gardner, this film stars Will Smith as a struggling salesman who becomes homeless while trying to provide for his son.\n\n2. **Slumdog Millionaire (2008)** - This film tells the story of a young man from the slums of Mumbai who competes on a quiz show and reflects on his life experiences, showcasing hope and perseverance.\n\n3. **12 Years a Slave (2013)** - Based on the true story of Solomon Northup, this harrowing film highlights resilience in the face of unimaginable adversity and the pursuit of freedom.\n\n4. **Hidden Figures (2016)** - This inspiring film highlights the contributions of three African American women mathematicians at NASA, demonstrating their crucial role in the success of early space missions.\n\n5. **The Theory of Everything (2014)** - This biographical drama chronicles the life of physicist Stephen Hawking, focusing on his relationship with his wife and his determination to overcome his illness.\n\n6. **A Beautiful Mind (2001)** - Based on the life of mathematician John Nash, the film explores his battle with schizophrenia and his journey toward recovery and eventual success.\n\n7. **Remember the Titans (2000)** - This sports drama encapsulates themes of racial integration and teamwork, telling the story of a high school football team overcoming adversity.\n\n8. **Life of Pi (2012)** - A visually stunning film about survival and faith, following a young man stranded on a lifeboat with a Bengal tiger for 227 days.\n\n9. **The Intouchables (2011)** - A French film that tells the heartwarming story of an unlikely friendship between a wealthy quadriplegic and his caregiver, emphasizing the importance of connection and joy.\n\n10. **Joy (2015)** - Inspired by the true story of Joy Mangano, the film follows a young woman who becomes a successful entrepreneur despite facing numerous challenges and setbacks.\n\nThese films span various genres and themes, but they all convey messages of hope, resilience, and the human spirit's ability to overcome obstacles.",
